LXD NOTES

sudo lxd init - to initialize lxd
lxc remote list - to list the remote server to pull images
lxc image list images: - to list the available images on the remote repo called images
lxc list - to list available running containers
lxc launch images:{name of the remote image}
lxc exec {container_name} - to launch into the container
lxc info - to view information of the container
lxc config set {container_name} boot.autostart 1 - to start the container automatically upon boot up
lxc config set {container_name} limits.memory [set value limits] - to limit memory ussage of the container
lxc config show {container_name} - to show container configuration
lxc config set {container_name} boot.autostart.delay 30 - to delay container startup
lxc config set {container_name} boot.autostart.order [arbitrary#] - startup order
lxc launch --vm --config security.secureboot=false images:{imagerepo} (vm name instance) - dissable secure boot

Managing Storage in LXD

lxc storage create <pool> <driver> source=path - create a new storage pool
lxc launch --storage=<poolName> --vm - to launch vm in a customize storage pool
lxc launch --vm --device root,size=25Gib images:ubuntu/23.04 u01 - to specify root size
lxc config show --expanded <vmName>
lxc storage volume create --type=block <pool> <volumeName> size=3GiB - Hot-plugging LXD VM Data Disks
lxc storage volume attach <pool> <volumeName> <vmName>
lxc storage volume delete <pool> <volumeName>

Resource Management

lxc --config limits.cpu=4
lxc --config limits.memory=8GiB

Network Management
lxc network forward create lxcbr0 {hostip} - to create a forwarding rule
lxc network port add lxcbrd0 {host ip} tcp {targe port} {vm ip} {listening port}
lxc network forward create lxbdr0 10.0.0.179 target_address=10.110.115.175 - create a forwarding rules
